    <h3><a name"shin pain"></a>Shin Pain</h3>
        <p>"No, not the political wing of the IRA."</p>
            <p><b>From Elaine Ward - <a href="eRaceWalk.com">NARF</a></b> - You may have heard that racewalkers "raise their toes"  before heel contact and be tensing and pulling back your toes to "help" get the forefoot up. Keep in mind that the raising of the forefoot is done by dorsi flexing your foot - that is flexing your ankle to raise your forefoot. Pulling your toes back doesn't do anything other than to add a lot of tension to your shin muscles. Try keeping your foot relaxed as you flex your ankle. You may well find it helps.</p>

